Session of 2025
HOUSE BILL No. 2224
By Representatives Simmons and Fairchild
2-4
1 AN ACT concerning crimes, punishment and criminal procedure; relating
2 to search and seizure; requiring a law enforcement officer executing a
3 search warrant to be properly uniformed and announce their presence
4 before entering; amending K.S.A. 22-2510 and repealing the existing
5 section.
6
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
8 Section 1. K.S.A. 22-2510 is hereby amended to read as follows: 22-
9 2510. (a) A search warrant may be executed at any time of any day or
10 night.
11 (b) A law enforcement officer executing a search warrant at a
12 dwelling shall be properly uniformed and shall knock on the door and
13 announce their presence in a manner reasonably expected to be heard by
14 the occupants of the dwelling before entering the dwelling to execute a
15 search warrant.
16 (c) For the purposes of this section, "dwelling" means a building, or
17 portion thereof, that is used or intended for use as a human habitation,
18 home or residence.
19 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 22-2510 is hereby repealed.
20 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
21 publication in the statute book.

